Me and @mikeyolexy created a video explaining the process of making these types of photos that will be uploaded in a few days! I’ve been feeling great creating art again, I can’t wait to share more with everyone. Which one do you guys like more? 👻 .

This past year and a half has been the worst and hardest part of my life. I am so sorry for my absence and all the people I have let down. Not only have I been dealing with the loss of my father 9 months ago and having my son 12 days ago, I have become a person i didn’t recognize and someone I never wanted to be. I developed a drinking and drug problem that I recently had to go get help for. I have now been sober a month! It may not seem long to some but it is a huge accomplishment for me and I am finally starting to feel like myself again. Depression, anger and anxiety led me down a path many go down and I’m happy to finally see some light. I know i still have a long road ahead of me but I am now motivated and ready to come back stronger and better than ever. Thank you for baring with me and to everyone who stuck around. The support I have means the world to me. I have big things coming up including a podcast, vlog and of course MORE PHOTOS! Here’s a photo of me getting back into the swing of things taken by my buddy @mikeyolexy! I can’t wait to be back to my full self and fix all my wrongs. Thank you for reading, this was a hard thing for me to admit and to come to terms with. I love all of you.

My son, Oliver L.Bryan McKenney born 4.19.19

I never knew a love like this until he entered my life. 👶🏻 ❤️
i died when you died.

ITS A BOY!!!! I couldn’t be more grateful to be bringing a baby boy in this world with one of the strongest women I know. 2019 is all about you, Oliver L.Bryan McKenney! I love you so much already and i can’t wait to start our little family with your mommy. 💙
Happy anniversary to my best friend and love of my life. I don’t know what I would do without you. Here’s to forever, you little fricker!

IM GOING TO BE A FATHER!! After loss there is life. I am so sorry for my absence not only “online” but in life. These last few months have been unimaginably emotional for me. As most  of you know I lost my father in August to his battle with cancer and last month I lost my grandfather. I have never felt sadness like i have but, somehow during all of this the universe has given @karaschneikart and I one of the best gifts life can give you, a baby! They say “a boy doesn’t become a man until he loses his father”, I believe in that and I am so ready for my first test. I love you @karaschneikart! Baby McKenney coming May 2019!!
